Tuymans - Centre Pompidou | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[Philadelphia Museum of Art]] | location=Cl\u00e9rmont Ferrand | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Friedrich Christian Flick Collection | Friedrich Christian Flick Collection, Hamburger Bahnhof - Museum f\u00fcr Gegenwart]], Berlin<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.fcflick-collection.com/kuenstler-werke/luc-tuymans |title=Luc Tuymans | first=|last = |date = | publisher=Friedrich Christian Flick Collection | location=Berlin | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n* [[Serralves | Fundacion de Serralves]], Porto<ref>{{cite web | last =  | first = | authorlink = | year = | url = https://www.serralves.pt/en/activities/marcel-broodthaers-and-luc-tuymans-in-the-serralves-collection/ | publisher = | title = Marcel Broodthaers and Luc Tuymans in the Serralves Collection, From 13 Oct. 2018 to 11 Nov. 2018 | accessdate = 25 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200325182611/https://www.serralves.pt/en/activities/marcel-broodthaers-and-luc-tuymans-in-the-serralves-collection/ | archivedate = 25 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*[[Hammer Museum]], Los Angeles\n*[[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]], Washington, DC\n* HVCCA - Hudson Valley Center for Contemporary Art, Peekskill, New York\n* [[Israel Museum | The Israel Museum, Jerusalem]], Jerusalem<ref>{{cite web | last =  | first = | authorlink =  | year =  | url = https://www.imj.org.il/en/artistec/luc-tuymans | publisher = The Israel Museum, Jerusalem | title = Nuclear Plant | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200325182233/https://www.imj.org.il/en/artistec/luc-tuymans | archivedate = 25 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* Kunstmuseen Krefeld, Germany\n* [[Mu.ZEE | Kunstmuseum aan zee (Mu.ZEE)]], Ostend, Belgium<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = | url = https://www.muzee.be/collection/data/K001797 | publisher = Mu.ZEE Kunstmuseum aan zee | title = Tuymans, Luc (\u00b0Mortsel, 1958) | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200325181847/https://www.muzee.be/collection/data/K001797 | archivedate = 25 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* [[Museum of Fine Arts Bern]], Bern\n*[[Kunstmuseum Wolfsburg]], Wolfsburg<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.kunstmuseum-wolfsburg.de/collection/luc-tuymans/|title=Luc Tuymans | first=|last = |date = | publisher=Luc Tuymans - [[Kunstmuseum Wolfsburg]] | location=Wolfsburg | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*LACMA [[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]], Los Angeles<ref>{{cite web | url=https://collections.lacma.org/node/158328 | title=Luc Tuymans: LACMA Collections | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]] | location=Los Angeles | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n* [[Louisiana Museum of Modern Art|Louisiana Museum]], Humlebaek, Denmark\n*[[Mus\u00e9e d'Arts de Nantes | Mus\u00e9e des Beaux-Arts de Nantes]], Nantes<ref>{{cite web | url=https://museedartsdenantes.nantesmetropole.fr/resultats-navigart.html?jcrRedirectTo=%2Fcms%2Frender%2Flive%2Ffr%2Fsites%2Fmuseedarts%2Fresultats-navigart.html&keywords=luc+tuymans |title=Mus\u00e9e d'arts : Accueil, R\u00e9sultats Navigart | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[Mus\u00e9e d'Arts de Nantes]] | location=Nantes | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Museum f\u00fcr Moderne Kunst]], Frankfurt \n*[[Museum of Contemporary Art, Antwerp]], Antwerp<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.muhka.be/programme/detail/968-the-collection/artist/129-luc-tuymans |title=Luc Tuymans | first=|last = |date = | publisher=M HKA Museum of Contemporary Art Antwerp | location=Antwerp | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n* [[Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago | Museum of Contemporary Art Chicago]], Chicago\n*[[The Museum of Modern Art]], New York<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.moma.org/artists/7520 | title=Luc Tuymans: MoMA | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[The Museum of Modern Art]] | location=New York | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*Over Holland Collection, the Netherlands\n*[[Philadelphia Museum of Art]], Philadelphia<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.philamuseum.org/collections/permanent/90237.html?mulR=515056708%7C1 |title=Philadelphia Museum of Art | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[Philadelphia Museum of Art]] | location=Philadelphia | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Pinakothek der Moderne]], Munich<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pinakothek.de/kunst/luc-tuymans/three-moons|title=Luc Tuymans | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[Pinakothek der Moderne]] | location=Munich | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[San Francisco Museum of Modern Art]], San Francisco<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.sfmoma.org/artist/Luc_Tuymans/ |title=Luc Tuymans \u00b7 SFMOMA | first=|last = |date = | publisher=[[San Francisco Museum of Modern Art]] | location=San Francisco | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst]], Ghent<ref>{{cite web | url=https://smak.be/nl/nieuws/werk-body-van-luc-tuymans-uit-smak-collectie-nu-te-zien-in-venetie |title=Werk 'Body' van Luc Tuymans uit S.M.A.K.-collectie nu te zien in Veneti\u00eb | first=|last = |date = | publisher=S.M.A.K. Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst | location=Ghent | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum]], New York<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.guggenheim.org/artwork/artist/luc-tuymans |title=Fruit Picnic | first=|last = |date=25 July 2013 | publisher=[[Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum]] | location=New York | accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Tate Gallery]], London<ref name=Tate2004/>\n}}\n\n==Catalogue raisonn\u00e9==\nIn 2019, a comprehensive catalogue raisonn\u00e9 edited by the art historian Eva Meyer-Hermann was published by the [[David Zwirner Gallery]] and [[Yale University Press]]. Tuymans\u2019 paintings dating from 1972 on \u2013 564 in total \u2013 are spread between three volumes. ''Volume I'' covers the 186 paintings done on canvas or hardboard between 1972 and 1994.<ref name=Volume12018/> ''Volume II'' covers 198 paintings on canvas or, on occasion, polyester or vinyl, between 1995 and 2006,<ref name=Volume22018/> and ''Volume III'' includes 180 works on canvas dating from 2007 to 2018.<ref name=Volume32018/>\n\n==Position in the art market==\nTuymans is represented by [[Zeno X]] Gallery in Antwerp and the [[David Zwirner Gallery]] in New York. According to an article published by ''[[Artprice]]'' in 2019, half of his auction turnover is generated in the United States, and 36% in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web | last =  | first = | authorlink = | year = 13 August 2019 | url = https://www.artprice.com/artmarketinsight/luc-tuymans-without-appearing-to-be | publisher = | title = Luc Tuymans\u2026 without appearing to be | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200228201609/https://www.artprice.com/artmarketinsight/luc-tuymans-without-appearing-to-be | archivedate = 28 February 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref> In May 2005, ''Sculpture'' (2000), part of Tuymans' ''Mwana Kitoko'' (''Beautiful White Man'') series, was sold at [[Christie's|Christie's New York]] for a record price.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = | url =https://www.christies.com/LotFinder/lot_details.aspx?intObjectID=4489891 | publisher = Christies | title = Post-War and Contemporary Art (Evening Sale), New York, 11 May 2005 | accessdate = 25 March 2020 | archiveurl = | archivedate = | url-status =| df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2005, he was listed 184 in the 'Top 500' selling artists, a ranking compiled by ''Artprice.''<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = 2006 | url = https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf/trends2006.pdf | page = 26 | publisher = Art Price | title =Art Market Trends, Tendances du march\u00e9 de l\u2019art | accessdate =| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200303093320/https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf/trends2006.pdf | archivedate = 3 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref> Tuymans\u2019 auction record dates back to Christie\u2019s May 2013 prestigious Contemporary Art sale in New York where ''Rumour'' (2001) attracted unexpected attention. It was the best ever auction result for a contemporary Belgian artist (i.e. born after 1945). Since then, his paintings have fetched ever-increasing sums. As a result, in 2016, Tuymans was ranked 60 in the ''[[ArtReview]]'' list of the 100 most powerful people in the art world'.<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = 2015 | url = https://artmarketinsight.wordpress.com/2015/01/23/art-market-the-week-in-numbers-luc-tuymans/ | publisher = | title = Art Market: The Week in Numbers (Luc Tuymans) | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200228201604/https://artmarketinsight.wordpress.com/2015/01/23/art-market-the-week-in-numbers-luc-tuymans/ | archivedate = 28 February 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2019, Tuymans gained a lot of exposure with his exhibition ''La Pelle'' at [[Palazzo Grassi]] in Venice. The market reacted accordingly and his works generated even higher turnover on the secondary market, a record year for the artist.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = 13 August 2019| url = https://www.artprice.com/artmarketinsight/luc-tuymans-without-appearing-to-be| publisher = Artprice| title = Luc Tuymans\u2026 without appearing to be| accessdate = 24 April 2020 | archiveurl = | archivedate =  | url-status = | df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2015, Tuymans ranked 168 on the 'TOP 500' Contemporary Artists 2014/2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20161024_02535927/luc-tuymans-zestigste-in-kunsttop-power-100 | title=Luc Tuymans zestigste in kunsttop \u2018Power 100\u2019 | date=24 October 2016 | publisher=Gazet Van Antwerpen. Antwerpen: Mediahuis | location=Antwerpen | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224115825/https://www.houstonpress.com/arts/luc-tuymans-nice-is-just-that-and-nothing-more-6599642 | archivedate=24 February 2020 | df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Jackie | last=Wullschlager |   title=The Painterly Pessimist | url=https://www.ft.com/content/bb3eba30-3563-11e0-aa6c-00144feabdc0 | format=Fee required | publisher=Financial Times | date=12 February 2011 | accessdate=24 February 2020 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027001745/http://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20161024_02535927/luc-tuymans-zestigste-in-kunsttop-power-100 | archivedate=27 October 2016 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> That year, he ranked 75 in the \u2018Top 500\u2019 best-selling artists worldwide.<ref>{{cite web | last =  | first = | authorlink =  | year = 2019 | url = https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf//the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019.pdf |  page = 38 | publisher = Artprice | title = The Contemporary Art Market Report in 2019 | accessdate = 25 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200303093315/https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf//the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019.pdf | archivedate = 3 March 2020 | url-status = live |  df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last =  | first = | authorlink =  | year = 2019 | url = https://www.artprice.com/artprice-reports/the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019/top-500-contemporary-artists/top-500-contemporary-artists-51-to-100/ | publisher = Artprice | title = Top 500 contemporary artists: #51 to #100 | accessdate = 25 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200303094826/https://www.artprice.com/artprice-reports/the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019/top-500-contemporary-artists/top-500-contemporary-artists-51-to-100 | archivedate = 3 March 2020 | url-status = live |  df=dmy-all }}</ref> This brought him into the top 100 most successful artists on the global secondary market. As a result he is regarded today as one of the most successful European artists, ranked alongside the Italian artists [[Rudolf Stingel]] and [[Maurizio Cattelan]], the Belgian artist [[Harold Ancart]], and eight German artists, including [[Albert Oehlen]].<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year =  2019| url = https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf//the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019.pdf | page = 20 | publisher = Artprice | title = The Contemporary Art Market Report in 2019 | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200303093315/https://imgpublic.artprice.com/pdf//the-contemporary-art-market-report-2019.pdf | archivedate = 3 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Recognition==\nIn 2007, Tuymans was appointed Commander of the [[Order of Leopold (Belgium)|Order of Leopold]] of Belgium by [[Albert II of Belgium|King Albert II]],<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61450 |supp=y|page=N14|date=30 December 2015}}</ref> in 2013, he was made a Foreign Honorary Member of [[The American Academy of Arts and Letters]] in New York,<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = | url = https://artsandletters.org/?s=Luc+Tuymans&restype=all | publisher = American Academy of Arts and Letters | title = Member: Luc Tuymans | accessdate = 20 March 2020 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200325202509/https://artsandletters.org/?s=Luc+Tuymans&restype=all | archivedate = 25 March 2020 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Omer | first = Tony | url = https://www.mvtimes.com/2013/03/20/ward-just-selected-american-academy-arts-letters-14842/ | accessdate  = 20 March 2020 | date = 20 March 2013 | work = New York Times Literary Supplement | title = Ward Just selected for the American Academy of the Arts & Letters | archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20180701172636/http://www.mvtimes.com/2013/03/20/ward-just-selected-american-academy-arts-letters-14842/ | archive-date = 1 July 2018 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>  and the [[Academy of Arts, Berlin|Academy of Arts]] (''Akademie der K\u00fcnste'') in [[Berlin]]. In 2019 he received the Medal of Honor from the International Congress of Contemporary Painting (ICOCEP) in Porto in Portugal. Tuymans holds several academic honours, including an honorary doctorate for overall cultural merit bestowed by the [[Royal College of Art]] in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title=Honorary Doctors |url=http://www.rca.ac.uk/more/our-history/college-honours/honorary-doctors/ |publisher=London: Royal College of Art |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150315030921/http://www.rca.ac.uk/more/our-history/college-honours/honorary-doctors/ |archivedate=15 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Convocation 2015|url=http://www.rca.ac.uk/news-and-events/convocation2015/|publisher=London: Royal College of Art [view from 18:18]|accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref> an honorary doctorate bestowed by the University of Arts in Pozna\u0144 in 2014, and an honorary doctorate for overall cultural merit bestowed by the [[University of Antwerp]] in 2006.<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web|title=Honorary Doctors |url=https://www.uantwerpen.be/nl/overuantwerpen/organisatie/eredoctoraten/voorbije-edities/eredoctoraten-2009-2000 |publisher=Antwerpen: University of Antwerp |accessdate=23 February 2020 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223004718/https://www.uantwerpen.be/nl/overuantwerpen/organisatie/eredoctoraten/voorbije-edities/eredoctoraten-2009-2000/|archivedate=23 February 2020 }}</ref> In 2008, Tuymans received the Max Beckmann Foundation award at the [[St\u00e4delschule]]. In 2000, he was a finalist for the [[The Vincent Award|Vincent van Gogh Biennial Award for Contemporary Art in Europe]] and won the Coutts Contemporary Art Foundation award in Zurich. In 2013, Tuymans was awarded the Flemish Culture Award for Visual Arts and in 2020 the Ultima award for 'General Cultural Merit'.<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web | url=https://www.ultimas.be/laureaat/luc-tuymans | title=Algemene culturele verdienste 2019, Luc Tuymans | date=18 February 2020 | publisher=Ministerie van de Vlaamse Gemeenschap, Departement Cultuur, Jeugd en Media | location = Brussel | accessdate=23 February 2020 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224152924/https://www.ultimas.be/laureaat/luc-tuymans | archivedate=24 February 2020 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 1998, he received the biannual Culture Prize Blanlin-Evrart from the [[KU Leuven|Catholic University of Leuven]].<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web | last = Staff writer| first = | authorlink = | year = 2002 | url = https://www.kuleuven.be/cultuur/prijs/archief/boek.htm | publisher = KU Leuven | title = Boek '10 Jaar Cultuurprijs KU Leuven' | accessdate =26 March 2020 | archiveurl = | archivedate = | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 2013, he was given the award of excellence for his artistic contributions to the fight against AIDS by the [[AmfAR, The Foundation for AIDS Research|AmfAR, The Foundation for AIDS Research Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | year = 2013 | url = http://twoxtwo.org/2013-honoree/ | publisher = TWO x TWO for AIDS and Art, Dallas | title = Honoree: Luc Tuymans | accessdate = | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140227145414/http://twoxtwo.org/2013-honoree/ | archivedate = 27 February 2014 | url-status = live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nTuymans was born in [[Mortsel]] near [[Antwerp]] on 14 June 1958, and he continues to live in Antwerp today. His father, Antoon Tuymans, was Belgian Flemish and his mother, Elisabeth Dam, was Dutch.<ref name=\"ilegems1\"/>\n\nIn 1995, he met the Venezuelan artist [[Carla Arocha]] while working on his first American show at [[The Renaissance Society]] in Chicago and four years later, in 1999, they married.<ref>{{in lang|nl}} {{cite web | url=https://www.demorgen.be/leven-liefde/kunstenares-carla-arocha-kijkt-met-bang-hart-naar-situatie-in-haar-geboorteland-ik-blijf-weg-uit-venezuela-om-er-niet-te-sterven~bc4e6f14 | title=Kunstenares Carla Arocha kijkt met bang hart naar situatie in haar geboorteland | first =  Danny | last=Ilegems | date = 22 February 2019 | publisher = De Morgen. Antwerpen: DPG Media nv/ | location=San Francisco|accessdate=14 August 2019|url-status=live | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200222130516/https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/A-talk-with-Luc-Tuymans-about-SFMOMA-show-3270737.php | archivedate=22 February 2020 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n*[[List of Belgian painters]]\n*[[New European Painting]]\n\n==References==\n{{Refbegin}}\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n<br>\n\n'''More references (selected monographies)'''\n{{columns-list|colwidth=35em|\n* {{cite book|last1 = Aliaga|first1 = Juan Vicente| last2 = Loock| first2 = Ulrich| last3 = Reust|first3 = Hans Rudolf|last4 = Spector|first4 = Nancy|author-link =|title = Luc Tuymans|publisher=[[Phaidon Press|Phaidon]]|series = | volume = | edition =Rev.|location = London|date = 2007|page =|isbn = 9780714842981|OCLC = }}\n* {{cite book|last1=Grynsztejn | first1 =Madeleine|last2 =Molesworth| first2 =Helen|author-link =|title =Luc Tuymans|publisher =San Francisco Museum of Modern Art ; Columbus: Wexner Center for the Arts|series =|volume = | edition =| location =San Francisco|date = 2009|page=|isbn =9781933045986|OCLC = 939221009}}\n* {{cite book|last1 = Meyer-Hermann|first1 = Eva|last2 = Tuymans| first2 =Luc|author-link=|title= Luc Tuymans: catalogue raisonn\u00e9 of the paintings. Volume 1: 1972-1994|publisher = [[David Zwirner Books]]; New Haven: [[Yale University Press]]|series =|volume =|edition =|location=New York|date=2018|page =492|isbn = \t9781941701614|OCLC = 1050148364}}\n* {{cite book|last1 = Meyer-Hermann|first1 = Eva|last2 = Tuymans|first2 =Luc|author-link=|title= Luc Tuymans: catalogue raisonn\u00e9 of the paintings. Volume 2, 1995-2006|publisher = [[David Zwirner Books]]; New Haven: [[Yale University Press]]|series =|volume = |edition =|location=New York|date=2019|page = 455|isbn = 9780300244670|OCLC = 1048937043}}\n* {{cite book|last1 = Meyer-Hermann|first1 = Eva|last2 = Tuymans| first2 =Luc|author-link=|title= Luc Tuymans: catalogue raisonn\u00e9 of the paintings. Volume 3, 2007-2018 | publisher = [[David Zwirner Books]]; New Haven: [[Yale University Press]]| series =|volume =|edition =|location=New York|date=2019|page = 425|isbn = 9780300247428|OCLC = 1048937043}}\n* {{cite book|last1 = Tuymans|first1 = Luc|last2=Loock| first2 =Ulrich|author-link=|title=Luc Tuymans: [Published on the occasion of an exhibition organized by Kunsthalle Bern, Bern, March 14\u2013April 26, 1992] | publisher=Kunsthalle|series =|volume=|edition=|location=Bern|date=1992|page=269| isbn = 9780714842981 | OCLC = 881709830 }}\n* {{cite book|last1=Tuymans | first1 =Luc|last2 =Helfenstein| first2 =Josef||last3 =Reust| first3 =Hans Rudolf|last4 =Rinder| first4 =Lawrence|author-link =|title =Luc Tuymans: Premonition, Zeichnungen/Drawings [Published on the occasion of an exhibition organized by Kunsthalle Bern, Bern, April 23\u2013June 29, 1997, Berkeley Art Museum, Oktober 10\u2013December 31, 1997; Capc Mus\u00e9e d'art contemporain, Bordeaux, January 30\u2013April 11, 1998]|publisher =Benteli |series =|volume = | edition =| location =Wabern-Bern, Germany|date = 1997|page= 208 |isbn =9783716510698|OCLC = 884075562}}\n* {{cite book|last1 =Tuymans|first1 =Luc|last2=Storr|first2 =Robert|last3 =Hoet | first3 =Jan|author-link = | title =Luc Tuymans: Mwana Kitoko, Beautiful White Man: [Published on the occasion of an exhibition organized by S.M.A.K Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst at the Belgian Pavilion in the Giardini of Venice, La Biennale di Venezia, Venice, June 10\u2013November 4, 2001] | publisher =S.M.A.K Stedelijk Museum voor Actuele Kunst | series = | volume=|edition = | location =Ghent, Belgium| date = 2001 | page = 135 | isbn =| OCLC = 496300303 }}\n* {{cite book | last1 =Tuymans| firs